{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "EDM techniques have been used to extract meaningful knowledge by combining big data sets of educational institutions with either Machine Learning or Deep Learning algorithms, or combining these two techniques to benefit students and improve their learning outcomes Shafiq et al (2022).",
    "The spread of the term EDM began in 2005, and was defined as \"an emerging discipline, concerned with developing methods for exploring the unique and increasingly large-scale data that come from educational settings and using those methods to better understand students\" (Educational Data Mining Community, 2021).",
    "There are two views that can be used to categorize AI performance prediction models: (1) from the perspective of the AI model, which focuses on improving the accuracy of the models by developing and validating the models to accurately predict learning performance; and (2) from the perspective of the educational application, which focuses on the effect of the models to support both instructors and students in enhancing the teaching and learning quality Ouyang et al (2023).",
    "These two views should be combined to create successful prediction models that form a loop between educational application and empirical research validation, along with AI model development and optimization Ouyang et al (2023); Wu et al (2022); Yang et al (2021).",
    "However, the majority of research on AI prediction models has focused on the creation and improvement of AI models, that is, employing several algorithms to create models with greater predictive accuracy Ouyang et al (2023)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "EDM techniques have been used to extract meaningful knowledge by combining big data sets of educational institutions with either Machine Learning or Deep Learning algorithms, or combining these two techniques to benefit students and improve their learning outcomes Shafiq et al (2022).",
